B^n\times\mathbb T^n
p=(p_1,\ldots,p_n)
B
q=(q_1,\ldots,q_n)
\mathbb T^n
\Omega=\sum_{i=1}^ndq_i\wedge dp_i,
H(q,p)=H_0(p)+\varepsilon H_1(q,p)
\omega_0(p):=\dfrac{\partial H_0}{\partial p}.
\det\left(\frac{\partial^2 H_0}{\partial q\partial q}\right)\neq 0
\dot p=-\varepsilon\frac{\partial H_1}{\partial q},\quad \dot q=\omega_0(p)+\varepsilon\frac{\partial H_1}{\partial p}
H=\mathrm{constant}
